This paper deals with object detection in autonomous driving scenarios, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method involves using neural networks to lift 2D images to 3D representations, which is a technique that falls under the umbrella of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions using a carefully designed training mechanism and automatically selected minimally noisy data, which suggests the use of optimization techniques and statistical learning (cs.NE).
